post_text:
Monday, September 14 is a fully remote day for ALL students, as are all Mondays at this time! However, on that day, our staff will be distributing materials for our students that are fully remote every day. That is their pick up day. So, there will be NO remote instruction happening on Monday, Sept. 14 so staff are available to help the fully remote students that day. There will be work and assignments posted ahead of time in Google Classroom for students to work on independently. Regular instruction will resume on Tuesday, Sept. 15 with Group A students in person and Group B students remote.

Please note that this is an exception. On most remote Mondays, there will be remote instruction happening. It is just this coming Monday, Sept. 14 that will be set up differently so our purely remote students have the chance to get their materials.

post_text:
A reminder to students wishing to audition for this year's fall comedy! In person auditions are by SIGN UP only for a specific time slot on Sunday, Sept. 13 between 1- 4 pm. Time slots are in 1/2 hour intervals and limited to 8 students per group. These auditions are for new students and those who really wish to gain more experience in auditioning.

If you have been performing for a while and are a veteran, you can simply fill out the audition form- email it in and you do NOT need to do an in person audition this time around. Audition forms being emailed or turned in need to be to Mrs. Finley BY 10 am on Sunday, Sept. 13. Any questions, please email!

post_text:
Dear Franklin Families,🎉🎉🎉

Happy May first! We are thrilled to share that we will be celebrating our families with a School-Community Parade on Wednesday, May 6th!

Staff from all three schools will be following the buses that deliver breakfast and lunch on Wednesday morning. There will be staff in the vehicles following all five bus routes beginning at 9 am. All buses will leave from FMS and will follow the routes as has been the practice!

We are thrilled to be given this opportunity to celebrate the work you have been doing, in addition to having the opportunity to see all of the little faces that we miss and cherish so much! We hope you can take a moment and step outside to wave or share a smile!

Please remember to follow the social distancing rules, as you wait for the parade to arrive at your stop!

We look forward to seeing everyone! Let’s hope for sunny weather!

See you soon!🎉🎉🎉🎉
PSS, FMS and FHS Staff

post_text:
To our FHS Seniors:

Dear Class of 2020 and their families,
We want you to know that we miss you and want to celebrate your accomplishments. We are ordering a banner to display the names of all the members of the Class of 2020 to be posted in front of the high school for all to see. In addition, we are ordering personalized lawn signs for each student to be placed either inside or outside your home. Thank you for continuing to demonstrate the GOLDEN attributes during remote learning. You will receive additional information as soon as possible about distribution of the personalized signs.
Congratulations FHS Class of 2020!
Principal Charette, Assistant Principal Schmidt, and the entire FHS Staff and Faculty

Dear Franklin Families,

We are pleased to share that the Franklin School Board approved our plan for the use of live feed video, Google Meet and Zoom, for use with our staff and students. This will be conducted on your personal devices including computers, tablets, and cell phones. This will not work on the district supplied chromebooks. These tools may be used for whole class, small group, and individualized check-ins and instruction. Please click on the link below and complete the short permission form to grant your student(s) access to this additional instruction. We are pleased to be able to provide this for your students to enhance their remote learning experience.. As always, contact me if you have any questions or concerns. Thank you for your continued support.

Sincerely,

Dan LeGallo
SAU 18 Superintendent
(603) 266-9833
dlegallo@gm.sau18.org

post_text:
Good Evening,
This is a very important message from the Superintendents Office at S.A.U. 18. Please read carefully.

This afternoon Governor Sununu extended remote learning until May 4, 2020. Food deliveries will continue as they have daily. There will be an emergency School Board Meeting on Tuesday night, March 31, 2020 at 6:00 PM at Franklin Middle School. We will be live streaming and adhering to the Governors request of no more than ten people assembled in one place at one time.

Please contact us if you have any questions. Again, thank you all for everything you are doing for the students of Franklin.

post_text:
PARENT MESSAGE
Franklin High School is engaging the city as it creates a Portrait of the Franklin Graduate. This process will help us clearly identify what a Franklin Graduate should know and do to ensure post high school success. Our first step is helping to understand what the experience has been for our most recent alumni.

Parents of recent alumni, we need your help. Please take a few minutes to complete this survey which is focused on how Franklin High School prepared your student (YOG 2015-2019) for life after high school. The survey will be open through March 31, 2020.

We are also conducting small focus groups and individual phone interviews March 16 through March 31 with some deeper questions. If you are interested in participating in one of these, please let us know in the survey.

Not a parent or guardian of a recent alumni and want to get involved, let us know how by completing this form.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/7N23KBC
shared_text:

Franklin NH Alumni Parent Survey
text:
PARENT MESSAGE
Franklin High School is engaging the city as it creates a Portrait of the Franklin Graduate. This process will help us clearly identify what a Franklin Graduate should know and do to ensure post high school success. Our first step is helping to understand what the experience has been for our most recent alumni.

Parents of recent alumni, we need your help. Please take a few minutes to complete this survey which is focused on how Franklin High School prepared your student (YOG 2015-2019) for life after high school. The survey will be open through March 31, 2020.

We are also conducting small focus groups and individual phone interviews March 16 through March 31 with some deeper questions. If you are interested in participating in one of these, please let us know in the survey.

Not a parent or guardian of a recent alumni and want to get involved, let us know how by completing this form.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/7N23KBC

post_text:
Dear Franklin Families,

I am pleased to share with you the good news that the Paul Smith Elementary School and Franklin Middle School have been selected for a visit from the Federal Department of Education in Washington, D.C. Next Wednesday, March 11th, Assistant Secretary of Education, Frank Brogan, will be visiting our schools as part of his three day visit to New Hampshire.

Our schools were selected at the request of New Hampshire Commissioner of Education, Frank Edelblut, for demonstrating great innovation and change to assist our high population of struggling learners.

We are excited to be recognized for our efforts to improve our school system and as always are thankful to our families and community for all of your support.

Sincerely,

Dan LeGallo
SAU 18 Superintendent
